# Auth and Session Rules

## Scope
- Auth logic lives in `apps/api/controllers/auth.controller.ts` and `apps/api/routes/auth.routes.ts`.
- Session typing is declared in `apps/api/global.d.ts`.
- Backend auth is API-first and token-based.

## Token Contract
- Protected endpoints use `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.
- `isAuth` validates `process.env.JWT_SECRET` and sets `req.user = { userId, status }`.
- Keep `req.user` typing aligned in `apps/api/global.d.ts`.

## Auth Route Surface
- `POST /auth/login`
- `POST /auth/login-twofa`
- `POST /auth/signup`
- `GET /auth/status` (guarded by `isAuth`)
- `GET /auth/profile`, `PUT /auth/profile` (guarded by `isAuth`)
- `GET /auth/2fa` (guarded by `isAuth`)
- `POST /auth/reset`
- `GET /auth/reset-password`, `POST /auth/reset-password`
- `POST /auth/webauthn/register/options` (guarded by `isAuth`)
- `POST /auth/webauthn/register/verify` (guarded by `isAuth`)
- `POST /auth/webauthn/authenticate/options`

## Controller Flow Expectations
- `postLogin`: validate input, verify password, return success token or MFA-required payload.
- `postLoginWithTwoFa`: verify state token and OTP code, then return access token.
- `postSignup`: validate input, create user + profile, send welcome email, return JSON success.
- `getStatus`: return current `req.user.status`.
- `getProfile` / `putProfile`: fetch and update `ProfileModel`.
- `get2FA`: generate TOTP secret, persist to `TwoFAModel`, return QR data URL.
- `postReset`: validate email and send reset email link.
- `getResetPassword`: validate token and return `_email` + `_token`.
- `postResetPassword`: hash and save new password (JWT reset flow, no `TokenModel` DB write/delete).
- WebAuthn flow uses `@simplewebauthn/server` and must keep RP ID aligned with `env.projectName`.
- `putProfile` handles disabling 2FA by deleting related `TwoFAModel` secrets.

## Do Not
- Do not store raw passwords.
- Do not return unguarded private profile/2FA data.
- Do not bypass `isAuth` for protected auth/admin routes.
- Do not move frontend login UI concerns into `apps/api`.
